videos.description: Asia Durr hits a long 3-pointer to give Louisville a 29-24 lead over UConn.
videos.headline: Durr sinks deep 3

videos.description: Asia Durr scores a 3-pointer with two defenders on her, leading to a 14-point 2nd quarter, going 4-of-8 from long range.
videos.headline: Durr lights up 2nd quarter with the deep ball

videos.description: UConn's Katie Lou Samuelson fakes a drive to the basket and instead tosses up an off-balance 3-pointer, drawing a foul.
videos.headline: Samuelson draws foul for 3-point attempt

videos.description: Asia Durr passes the ball over her head to Arica Carter, who finds Sam Fuehring for the layup in transition.
videos.headline: Louisville's good ball handling leads to bucket

videos.description: After a five-minute draught for UConn, Napheesa Collier drives to the basket for a layup while drawing a foul.
videos.headline: Collier completes 3-point play

videos.description: The Louisville Cardinals beat the UConn Huskies 78-69, their first win against UConn since 1993.
videos.headline: Louisville defeats UConn for 1st time since 1993

videos.description: Louisville coach Jeff Walz reflects on his first victory over UConn as the head coach of the Cardinals.
videos.headline: Walz: This is a 'great group of kids'
